.TH "NETFYR.YAML" 5 "" "" "File Formats Manual"
.SH NAME
netfyr.yaml \- netfyr policy file formats
.SH DESCRIPTION
netfyr reads YAML files from
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/
to configure network interfaces.
This page documents all supported YAML formats and their fields.
.PP
Files may contain multiple YAML documents separated by
.BR \-\-\- .
Each document is parsed independently and produces one policy.
.PP
For worked configuration examples, see
.BR netfyr\-examples (7).
.SH "BARE STATE FORMAT"
The simplest format.
A YAML document with no
.B kind
field declares the desired state of a single network entity.
It is automatically wrapped into a static policy with default priority 100
and a name derived from the filename.
.PP
All properties are written at the top level in a flat format:
.B type
and selector properties (see
.BR SELECTORS )
identify the target entity, and configuration properties (see
.BR FIELDS )
declare its desired state.
.PP
Fields:
.TP
.B type
(string, required)
The entity type.
Currently supported:
.BR ethernet .
.TP
.B "Selector properties (at top level)"
See
.B SELECTORS
below.
Fields:
.BR name ,
.BR driver ,
.BR mac ,
.BR pci_path .
.TP
.B "Configuration properties (at top level)"
See
.B FIELDS
below.
For ethernet:
.BR mtu ,
.BR addresses ,
.BR routes ,
.BR state .
.PP
Example:
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
name: eth0
mtu: 1500
addresses:
  - 10.0.1.50/24
.fi
.RE
.SH "POLICY FORMAT"
A YAML document with
.BR "kind: policy" .
Provides explicit control over the factory type, priority, and naming.
.PP
Fields:
.TP
.B kind
(string, required)
Must be
.BR policy .
.TP
.B name
(string, required)
Unique policy name.
Used in conflict reports and provenance tracking.
.TP
.B factory
(string, required)
Factory type.
One of:
.BR static ,
.BR dhcpv4 .
.RS
.TP
.B static
Produces states from the literal
.B state
or
.B states
fields defined in this policy.
.TP
.B dhcpv4
Acquires an address via DHCPv4 for the interface identified by
.BR selector .
Requires the netfyr daemon to be running.
.RE
.TP
.B priority
(integer, optional, default: 100)
Numeric priority for field-level conflict resolution.
Higher values take precedence when two policies set the same field on the
same interface.
.TP
.B selector
(mapping, required for dhcpv4)
Identifies the target interface.
Used with
.BR "factory: dhcpv4" .
For static policies, selector fields are written inside
.B state
or
.B states
instead.
See
.B SELECTORS
below for the available fields.
.TP
.B state
(mapping, optional)
A single entity state definition in flat format, with the same structure as
the bare state format.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR states .
Used with
.BR "factory: static" .
.TP
.B states
(sequence, optional)
A list of entity state definitions in flat format.
Used when a policy produces multiple entities.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR state .
Used with
.BR "factory: static" .
.PP
Example (static, single state):
.RS 4
.nf
kind: policy
name: server\-network
factory: static
priority: 150
state:
  type: ethernet
  name: eth0
  mtu: 9000
  addresses:
    - 10.0.1.50/24
.fi
.RE
.PP
Example (static, multiple states):
.RS 4
.nf
kind: policy
name: server\-network
factory: static
priority: 150
states:
  - type: ethernet
    name: eth0
    mtu: 9000
    addresses:
      - 10.0.1.50/24
  - type: ethernet
    name: eth1
    mtu: 1500
.fi
.RE
.PP
Example (dhcpv4):
.RS 4
.nf
kind: policy
name: eth0\-dhcp
factory: dhcpv4
selector:
  name: eth0
.fi
.RE
.SH "MULTI-DOCUMENT FILES"
A single YAML file may contain multiple documents separated by
.BR \-\-\- .
Each document is parsed independently and produces one policy.
.PP
Example:
.RS 4
.nf
type: ethernet
name: eth0
mtu: 9000
---
type: ethernet
name: eth1
mtu: 1500
.fi
.RE
.SH SELECTORS
Selector fields identify which system entity a state targets.
They are written at the top level of a state definition, alongside the
.B type
and configuration fields.
All specified selector fields must match (AND logic).
.TP
.B name
(string)
Exact interface name (e.g.,
.BR eth0 ).
.TP
.B driver
(string)
Kernel driver name (e.g.,
.BR ixgbe ).
.TP
.B pci_path
(string)
PCI device path (e.g.,
.BR 0000:03:00.0 ).
.TP
.B mac
(string)
MAC address in colon-separated hexadecimal (e.g.,
.BR aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff ).
Comparison is case-insensitive.
.PP
Note: In
.B dhcpv4
policies, selector fields are wrapped in a
.B selector:
mapping at the policy level rather than inside a state block, because the
policy-level
.B name
field would otherwise collide with the interface name selector.
.SH FIELDS
Configuration fields are written at the top level of a state definition,
alongside the
.B type
and selector properties.
The available fields depend on the entity type.
.SS Ethernet
The following fields apply to
.BR "type: ethernet" .
.TP
.B mtu
(integer)
Maximum transmission unit in bytes.
Valid range: 68\(en65535.
.TP
.B addresses
(sequence of strings)
IPv4 addresses assigned to the interface, in CIDR notation
(e.g.,
.BR 10.0.1.50/24 ).
Order is preserved: the first address becomes the primary (source) address.
Duplicate addresses are rejected.
IPv6 is not supported.
.TP
.B routes
(sequence of mappings)
Static routes to configure.
Each route mapping supports the following keys:
.RS
.TP
.B destination
(string, required)
Route destination in CIDR notation (e.g.,
.BR 0.0.0.0/0 ).
.TP
.B gateway
(string, optional)
Next-hop IP address (e.g.,
.BR 10.0.1.1 ).
.TP
.B metric
(integer, optional)
Route metric (lower values are preferred).
.RE
.TP
.B state
(string)
Administrative state of the interface.
Accepted values:
.BR up ,
.BR down .
.SH "VALUE TYPES"
YAML scalars are mapped to netfyr internal types as follows:
.TP
.B "YAML boolean"
netfyr
.B Bool
.TP
.B "YAML integer >= 0"
netfyr
.B U64
.TP
.B "YAML integer < 0"
netfyr
.B I64
.TP
.B "YAML string (valid IPv4 address)"
netfyr
.B IpAddr
(e.g.,
.BR 10.0.0.1 )
.TP
.B "YAML string (valid IPv4 CIDR prefix)"
netfyr
.B IpNetwork
(e.g.,
.BR 10.0.0.0/24 )
.PP
IPv6 addresses are not supported.
Strings containing IPv6 addresses (e.g.,
.BR fe80::1 )
are treated as plain strings and will fail schema validation if used in
address fields.
.TP
.B "YAML string (other)"
netfyr
.B String
.TP
.B "YAML sequence"
netfyr
.B List
.TP
.B "YAML mapping"
netfyr
.B Map
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/netfyr/policies/
Policy and bare state YAML files.
Loaded at daemon startup and when
.B netfyr apply
is invoked.
.TP
.I /var/lib/netfyr/policies/
Daemon-persisted policies managed automatically by the netfyr daemon.
Do not edit these files by hand.
